Package gw.api.rest

Class MediaType

java.lang.Object
gw.api.rest.MediaType
public class MediaType extends Object
The MediaType class represents a parsed MIME type, such as "application/json" or "text/*". Two MediaTypes can be compared for strict equality, but it's generally more correct to compare them for compatibility instead, since the types "application/json" and "application/json; charset=UTF-8" are technically not equal but are compatible. Similarly, "text/*" is compatible with all text media types regardless of subtype.

    • getParameters

      @NotNull public @NotNull Map<String,String> getParameters()
      Returns the parameters for this MediaType, i.e. the map of name/value pairs following the ";" character. In the "application/json; charset=UTF-8" type, the parameter map will have one value with "charset" as the key and "UTF-8" as the value. This map may be empty.
      Returns:
      the Map of parameter values for this media type

    • isCompatible

      public boolean isCompatible(@NotNull @NotNull MediaType other)
      Returns true if two MediaTypes are considered compatible. For two media types to be compatible, both the type and subtype must either be equal or one of them much be *. Parameters are not considered when determining compatibility. The compatibility check is commutative.
      Parameters:
      other - the other MediaType to check
      Returns:
      true if this type is compatible with the other type, false otherwise
